 2025.", "score": 0.7975099, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.heattreattoday.com/u-s-steel-nippon-steel-merger-will-expand-u-s-steels-technical-base", "title": "U. S. Steel-Nippon Steel Merger Will Expand Pittsburgh Steelmaker\'s Technical Base - Heat Treat Today", "content": "would acquire Pittsburgh\\u2013based U. S. Steel. Under the deal, Nippon Steel would acquire the company for $14.1 billion, which totals to $14.9 billion when including the assumption of U.S. Steel\\u2019s debt. As part of the deal, Nippon Steel will invest $1.4 billion in U. S. Steel\\u2019s assets and will share technical knowledge, stated Burritt during his keynote address to the 2024 Global Steel Dynamics Forum.\\n\\n\\u201cThey\\u2019re experts in integrated mills, and they want to invest here,\\u201d he said.", "score": 0.79293, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://gmk.center/en/news/biden-plans-to-block-the-merger-of-nippon-steel-and-us-steel-bloomberg", "title": "Biden plans to block the merger of Nippon Steel and US Steel - Bloomberg", "content": "In early December, Nippon Steel reaffirmed its confidence that the acquisition of US Steel could be completed by the end of 2024 if the deal goes through the proper procedures and is approved by the Biden administration.\\n\\nAs GMK Center reported earlier, Japanese Prime Minister Shigeru Ishiba, according to Reuters, sent a letter to the US President asking him to approve the deal so as not to harm recent efforts to strengthen ties between the two countries.\\n\\nTags:", "score": 0.741169, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://finance.yahoo.com/news/us-steel-nippon-steel-merger-102356390.html", "title": "US Steel and Nippon Steel merger gains non-US regulator approval", "content": "These approvals from the regulatory bodies mark a crucial step towards the completion of the deal, which is anticipated in the second half of 2024.\\n\\nThe bodies approving the transaction include the Directorate-General for Competition of the European Commission, the Mexican Federal Economic Competition Commission, the Serbian Competition Commission, the Ministry of Economy of Slovakia, and the Turkish Competition Authority.", "score": 0.7089592, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.mining-technology.com/news/us-steel-nippon-steel-merger", "title": "US Steel, Nippon Steel merger gains nod of non-US regulators", "content": "United States Steel Corporation (US Steel) and Nippon Steel have secured all regulatory clearances from jurisdictions outside of the US for their proposed merger.\\n\\nThese approvals from the regulatory bodies mark a crucial step towards the completion of the deal, which is anticipated in the second half of 2024.\\n\\n### Go deeper with GlobalData\\n\\nReportsLogo\\n\\n#### Mining Industry Mergers and Acquisitions Deals by Top Themes in Q1 ...\\n\\nReportsLogo", "score": 0.6932451, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.wesa.fm/politics-government/2025-02-07/trump-us-steel-nippon-investment", "title": "Trump says Nippon Steel will invest in US Steel, instead of buying it | 90.5 WESA", "content": "# Trump says US Steel will get investment from Nippon Steel, instead of being bought by it\\n\\nPresident Donald Trump answers questions during a news conference with Japan\'s Prime Minister Shigeru Ishiba at the White House, Friday, Feb. 7, 2025, in Washington. (AP Photo/Evan Vucci)\\n\\nPresident Donald Trump on Friday suggested that Nippon Steel would no longer buy U.S. Steel as planned, but the Japanese company would instead invest in the symbolically important American business.", "score": 0.6912478, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.wesa.fm/politics-government/2025-02-07/trump-us-steel-nippon-investment?00000178-d1bf-df3e-a1f9-d9ff71f60001-p=2", "title": "Trump says Nippon Steel will invest in US Steel, instead of buying it | 90.5 WESA", "content": "# Trump says US Steel will get investment from Nippon Steel, instead of being bought by it\\n\\nPresident Donald Trump answer