s for $14.9B Merger", "content": "The U.S. Department of Justice is rigorously examining the proposed transaction. In response to the mounting concerns, Nippon Steel has pledged to honor all existing agreements between U.S. Steel and the union. Additionally, Nippon Steel has committed to relocating its U.S. headquarters to Pittsburgh, where U.S. Steel is currently based, in a bid to alleviate some of the apprehensions surrounding the merger.", "score": 0.5820878, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://nwindianabusiness.com/community/business-news/u-s-steel-stockholders-approve-merger-with-nippon-steel/64321", "title": "U.S. Steel stockholders approve merger with Nippon Steel \\u2022 Northwest Indiana Business Magazine", "content": "U.S. Steel has operations across the U.S. and in Central Europe. The steelmaker serves the automotive, construction, appliance, energy, containers and packaging industries. U.S. Steel has an annual raw steelmaking capability of 22.4 million net tons. The company was founded in 1901.\\n\\nBarclays Capital Inc., Goldman Sachs & Co. LLC and Evercore Inc. are serving as financial advisers to U. S. Steel. Milbank LLP and Wachtell, Lipton, Rosen & Katz are acting as legal advisers.", "score": 0.580091, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://srnnews.com/yellen-says-cfius-made-thorough-analysis-of-blocked-us-steel-nippon-steel-merger", "title": "Yellen says CFIUS made thorough analysis of blocked US Steel-Nippon Steel merger - SRN News", "content": "By David Lawder\\n\\nWASHINGTON (Reuters) -U.S. Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen said on Wednesday that Nippon Steel\\u2019s planned acquisition of U.S. Steel received a \\u201cthorough analysis\\u201d by an interagency review body that was sent to President Joe Biden, who blocked the deal on national security grounds.", "score": 0.55478466, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.france24.com/en/tv-shows/business/20250106-nippon-steel-and-us-steel-sue-biden-administration-usw-and-cleveland-cliffs-over-blocked-merger-deal", "title": "Nippon Steel, US Steel sue Biden administration over blocked merger deal - Business - France 24", "content": "US Steel and Nippon Steel have filed lawsuits in Washington in a bid to overturn last week\'s decision by the Biden administration to block their planned merger. In a scathing statement, the steelmakers accused the outgoing president of making the move for political gain. They also sued the USW union and rival bidder Cleveland-Cliffs, accusing them of colluding to kill the deal to try to monopolise the US steel industry. Also in this edition: a 276 kg bluefin tuna fetches \\u20ac1.2 million at a New", "score": 0.45377067, "raw_content": null}]',
