e companies argue that the block not only affects their business interests but also disrupts the global steel industry\\u2019s dynamics.", "score": 0.7825466, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://finimize.com/content/us-steel-and-nippon-steel-eye-14-billion-merger-and-investment", "title": "US Steel And Nippon Steel Eye $14 Billion Merger And Investment - Finimize", "content": "Research\\n   News\\n   Guides\\n   Markets\\n   Events\\n   For Business\\n    and Japan\'s Nippon Steel are on track for a significant merger, eyeing big investments in America\'s industrial heartland. Nippon Steel has already offered to buy US Steel at $55 per share, now considering upping its commitment to revitalize Rust Belt facilities up to $7 billion. This strategic move targets enhanced steel production and infrastructure modernization. While o..", "score": 0.7467494, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://journal-neo.su/2024/10/10/on-the-political-issues-and-problems-related-to-the-planned-merger-between-nippon-steel-and-us-steel", "title": "Merger of Nippon Steel and US Steel: an important event for the industry", "content": "continued to deteriorate. Eventually, the purchased asset became a heavy burden on Toshiba, which finally sold it off in 2018. However, the consequences of carrying this burden for more than a decade had a very bad effect on a corporation which was once one of the pillars of the postwar Japanese economy.", "score": 0.7306941, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.foxbusiness.com/politics/trump-biden-oppose-nippon-us-steel-merger-what-vp-harris-position", "title": "Where does VP Harris stand on US Steel-Nippon Steel merger? | Fox Business", "content": "U.S. Steel has said its deal with Nippon Steel would strengthen the American steel industry and benefit workers as well as supply chains. (Justin Merriman/Bloomberg via Getty Images / Getty Images)\\n\\nNippon Steel, which is based in Japan but is not a state-owned enterprise, has worked with U.S. Steel in an effort to assuage the concerns about the merger raised by politicians and labor groups.", "score": 0.7171114, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://finance.yahoo.com/news/us-steel-nippon-steel-merger-102356390.html", "title": "US Steel and Nippon Steel merger gains non-US regulator approval", "content": "US Steel president and CEO David Burritt said: \\"We are pleased with the regulatory approvals received, as they are a clear indication that the transaction with Nippon Steel is pro-competitive and supports the strategic merits of foreign investment.\\n\\n\\"Together with Nippon Steel, US Steel will become a world-leading steelmaker with enhanced technologies and resources to support a stronger steel industry with enhanced competition.", "score": 0.6844544, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.mining-technology.com/news/us-steel-nippon-steel-merger", "title": "US Steel, Nippon Steel merger gains nod of non-US regulators", "content": "US Steel president and CEO David Burritt said: \\u201cWe are pleased with the regulatory approvals received, as they are a clear indication that the transaction with Nippon Steel is pro-competitive and supports the strategic merits of foreign investment.\\n\\n\\u201cTogether with Nippon Steel, US Steel will become a world-leading steelmaker with enhanced technologies and resources to support a stronger steel industry with enhanced competition.", "score": 0.6765563, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://nwindianabusiness.com/community/business-news/u-s-steel-stockholders-approve-merger-with-nippon-steel/64321", "title": "U.S. Steel stockholders approve merger with Nippon Steel \\u2022 Northwest Indiana Business Magazine", "content": "U.S. Steel has operations across the U.S. and in Central Europe. The steelmaker serves the automotive, construction, appliance, energy, containers and packaging industries. U.S. Steel has an annual raw steelmaking capability of 22.4 million net tons. The company was founded in 1901.\\n\\nBarclays Capital Inc., Goldman Sachs & Co. LLC and Evercore Inc. are serving as financial advisers to U. S. Steel. Milbank LLP and Wachtell, Lipton, Rosen & Katz are acting as legal advisers.", "score": 0.6755297, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://worldbusinessoutlook.com/nippon-steel-announces-major-business-restructuring", "title": "Nippon Steel announces major business restructuring \\u00bb World Business Outlook", "content": "Under the plan, Nippon Steel Metal Products will take over the commercial rights for construction steel pipes currently held by Nippon Steel Pipe through a company split. Meanwhile, Nippon Steel will absorb Nippon Steel Pipe\\u2019s mechanical steel pipe business through a merger.", "score": 0.6565047, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.pymnts.com/cpi-posts/us-steel-and-nippon-steel-secure-international-approvals-for-14-9b-merger", "title": "US Steel and Nippon Steel Secure International Approvals for $14.9B Merger", "content": "\\u0394\\n\\nNippon Steel secured the deal to acquire U.S. Steel last December, outbidding several rivals including Cleveland-Cliffs, ArcelorMittal and Nucor. This acquisition, valued at nearly $15 billion, represents a major consolidation in the steel sector, promising to reshape the market landscape significantly.", "score": 0.6490677, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://thehill.com/opinion/white-house/5061395-us-steel-nippon-steel-merger", "title": "Why Trump should switch sides on the US Steel-Nippon Steel merger (but probably won\\u2019t)", "content": "The US Steel-Nippon combination would push the company to third among world steel producers, behind fast-shrinking Arcelor Mittal. With a small manufacturing footprint in the United States, the likelihood of consolidation in the U.S. is much lower than with Cliffs, which operates over 20 steel-producing sites. And, under Cliffs, all the white-collar staff is almost certainly gone.", "score": 0.63316137, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://gmk.center/en/news/biden-plans-to-block-the-merger-of-nippon-steel-and-us-steel-bloomberg", "title": "Biden plans to block the merger of Nippon Steel and US Steel - Bloomberg", "content": "In early December, Nippon Steel reaffirmed its confidence that the acquisition of US Steel could be completed by the end of 2024 if the deal goes through the proper procedures and is approved by the Biden administration.\\n\\nAs GMK Center reported earlier, Japanese Prime Minister Shigeru Ishiba, according to Reuters, sent a letter to the US President asking him to approve the deal so as not to harm recent efforts to strengthen ties between the two countries.\\n\\nTags:", "score": 0.55449516, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://stainless-steel-world.net/nippon-steel-and-nippon-steel-stainless-steel-corporation-merger", "title": "Nippon Steel and Nippon Steel Stainless Steel Corporation merger - Stainless Steel World", "content": "The reason for the merger is to strengthen both companies in an increasingly challenging business environment, with a decline in domestic demand, overcapacity in the Asian market and the requirement for decarbonization, but also to be able to focus on new energy fields such as hydrogen and ammonia, where demand is expected to grow in the future.\\n\\n#### RELATED ARTICLESMORE FROM AUTHOR\\n\\nCompany News\\n\\n### Satyan Kumar takes charge as ONGC Director (Strategy)\\")\\n\\nCompany News", "score": 0.54303354, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.france24.com/en/tv-shows/business/20250106-nippon-steel-and-us-steel-sue-biden-administration-usw-and-cleveland-cliffs-over-blocked-merger-deal", "title": "Nippon Steel, US Steel sue Biden administration over blocked merger deal - Business - France 24", "content": "US Steel and Nippon Steel have filed lawsuits in Washington in a bid to overturn last week\'s decision by the Biden administration to block their planned merger. In a scathing statement, the steelmakers accused the outgoing president of making the move for political gain. They also sued the USW union and rival bidder Cleveland-Cliffs, accusing them of colluding to kill the deal to try to monopolise the US steel industry. Also in this edition: a 276 kg bluefin tuna fetches \\u20ac1.2 million at a New", "score": 0.528899, "raw_content": null}]',
